      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOLDEN SHOOZ (3) is a newcomer to the Grant Dixon yard from Victoria where she was fourth in the Group 2 Breeders Crown 3F Final when last seen four months ago. Capable mare who was readied with two trials here, winning the latest. Ideally drawn and could kick off in Queensland with a win. DRAW A DREAM (1) got back on track when third last week, beaten 4.5 metres. That was her third placing from her last four starts so her hoof is on the till. Gets her chance from the ace draw. TOUGH SHAZ (6) is another building towards a win and could be ready to deliver after coming from a similar barrier last time out when runner-up at this venue. LULLABY NZ (7) draws wider than in her last-start fourth but recorded a series of placings prior so must be included.",
